## Codebase Context

### Project Identity
- **Anvil** is an AI coding agent (multi-agent architecture, REPL-based)  
- **Saguaro** is the semantic code intelligence engine (indexing, semantic search, verification, impact analysis)
- **HighNoon** is the C++ LLM inference framework (CPU-first, SIMD-centric)

### Architecture
```
Anvil/
├── core/              # Agent core: loops, planning, execution, tools
│   └── native/        # C++ native extensions (SIMD ops, TensorFlow custom ops)
├── saguaro/           # Semantic code intelligence engine
│   ├── indexing/       # Code indexing, embeddings, vector search
│   ├── ops/            # Python wrappers for C++ operations
│   ├── storage/        # Vector store, index persistence
│   └── dni/            # Direct Native Interface (agent communication)
├── agents/            # Agent role definitions, orchestration
├── cli/               # Command-line interface, REPL
├── config/            # Configuration system (settings.py)
├── tools/             # Agent tools (file ops, code analysis, search)
├── domains/           # Domain knowledge modules
├── prompts/           # Prompt templates and prompt engineering
│   ├── GEMINI.md      # Current standards foundation
│   └── shared_prompt_foundation.md  # Shared audit prompt
├── docs/              # Documentation and workflows
│   └── workflows/     # Agent workflow SOPs
├── tests/             # Test suite
├── infrastructure/    # Build, deployment, CI/CD
├── benchmarks/        # Performance benchmarks
├── Saguaro/           # Saguaro C++ source (libsaguaro)
│   ├── src/           # C++ source files
│   └── include/       # C++ headers
└── scripts/           # Utility scripts
```

### Key Technical Facts
- **Languages**: Python 3.12+, C++17
- **Compute model**: CPU-first, SIMD-first (AVX2 primary, AVX-512/NEON secondary)
- **No GPU dependency**: All hot paths must be CPU-optimized
- **Testing framework**: `pytest` for Python, CMake-based for C++
- **Linting**: `ruff` for Python
- **Code intelligence**: Saguaro provides `query`, `verify`, `skeleton`, `slice`, `impact`, `deadcode` commands
- **Existing verification**: Saguaro has a `verify` command with engines: `native` (regex patterns), `ruff` (linter), `semantic` (drift detection)
- **Agent governance**: Existing GEMINI.md and shared_prompt_foundation.md define current rules

### Current Standards Enforcement
The project currently enforces standards through:
1. **`prompts/GEMINI.md`** — Agent-facing policy document (read by AI at session start)
2. **`prompts/shared_prompt_foundation.md`** — Shared audit prompt foundation
3. **`saguaro verify`** — Automated verification with native/ruff/semantic engines
4. **`.saguaro.rules`** — Rule definitions for the native verification engine
5. **`ruff.toml`** — Python linter configuration
6. **Manual agent protocols** — Red-team, spec-interview, chronicle

